      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T13:58:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This gives me some pause because of issues images with crossing recording contexts, even if they\u0027re in the same \"family\". If we made this on a direct context then it\u0027s ok to use with another context in the family but not if made on a non-direct-recording context (and hasn\u0027t yet hit the direct context).\n\nI wasn\u0027t sure how to check it. We have SkImage::isValid(GrRecordingContext*) but it suffers the same problem.",
