        "id": 10796
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T14:33:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems like the kind of thing that may come up again and again.\n\n- The bare minimum move is to use `matches()` just to keep in line with all the other checks of this kind.\n- The practical safe move is to add a flag indicating that the image came from the \ndirect context.\n- The larger architectural move may be to move toward an _actual_ context ID (as opposed to the family ID) that we can tack on to any resource to indicate family ID + type of originating context.\n\nThoughts?",
